SIMPLE: momental
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Momental
<hw>Mo*men"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>momental</ets>.]</ety> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lasting
but a moment; brief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not one <qex>momental</qex> minute doth she swerve.</q>
<rj><qau>Breton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Important; momentous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to moment or
momentum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Momentally</ent>⟦br⟧
